    <section class="section">
      <div class="container grid2">
        <div class="card pad">
          <h2>Non-surgical care</h2>
          <p class="muted">Many shoulder problems improve with a focused plan and time.</p>
          <div class="hr"></div>
          <ul>
            <li>Activity modification and education</li>
            <li>Physical therapy guidance and home exercise plan</li>
            <li>Anti-inflammatory strategies when appropriate</li>
            <li>Injections when indicated (based on diagnosis and goals)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card pad">
          <h2>Arthroscopy</h2>
          <p class="muted">Minimally invasive surgery for a range of shoulder injuries.</p>
          <div class="hr"></div>
          <ul>
            <li>Rotator cuff repair</li>
            <li>Labral repair / stabilization for instability</li>
            <li>Biceps procedures (when appropriate)</li>
            <li>Debridement for select problems</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card pad">
          <h2>Rotator cuff repair</h2>
          <p class="muted">Discussed when tear pattern, symptoms, and function warrant surgical repair.</p>
          <div class="hr"></div>
          <ul>
            <li>Traumatic tears with weakness</li>
            <li>Persistent pain after appropriate rehab</li>
            <li>Clear expectations for sling use and rehab milestones</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card pad">
          <h2>Instability treatment</h2>
          <p class="muted">Options range from rehab to stabilization for recurrent dislocations.</p>
          <div class="hr"></div>
          <ul>
            <li>Return-to-play planning for athletes</li>
            <li>Stabilization when recurrent instability persists</li>
            <li>Imaging review to guide best approach</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card pad">
          <h2>Arthritis care</h2>
          <p class="muted">Start with symptom control; consider surgical options when daily function is limited.</p>
          <div class="hr"></div>
          <ul>
            <li>Education and activity adjustments</li>
            <li>Targeted non-surgical symptom management</li>
            <li>Shoulder replacement consultation when indicated</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card pad">
          <h2>Second opinions</h2>
          <p class="muted">A clear review of diagnosis, timing, and expected outcomes.</p>
          <div class="hr"></div>
          <ul>
            <li>Bring prior imaging (X-ray/MRI) and reports</li>
            <li>Review prior PT/injection/surgical recommendations</li>
            <li>Align treatment to your goals and lifestyle</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
